TEXT(&beginproblem);

$a=random(2,9,1); 
$b=random(2,9,1); 
$x=random(2,9,1); 

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR Let the function \(f\) be defined by
\[f(x) = $a x + $b. \]
Then \(f(x+1) =\) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
EOT
&ANS(multivar_function_cmp("$a*(x+1)+$b",["x"]));
$x++;
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and
\(f(x-1) =\) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
EOT
&ANS(multivar_function_cmp("$a*(x-1)+$b",["x"]));

TEXT(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR Hint:
For the first question, take the definition of \(f(x)\), replace \(x\) with 
\((x+1)\), and simplify.
EOT



